rComments: He was a great professor! I took this course as a credit and I don't regret it, I enjoyed it so much I plan to take another philosophy course! We don't use a textbook for this course as he said he didn't want us to spend so much on one which is a real help since textbooks are so expensive!
He was a great professor for a course that may not always be easy or interesting. He posts everything online, however, I would come just for the fun because he is very funny

amazing professor. took this first year for a credit and although the course material is extremely boring, everything is posted online as well as lecture handout (so you don't even have to take notes). tutorials are easy as well. He's very funny and likeable.

He teaches both introductory courses and more technical courses in analytic philosophy. It's important to remember this: his interests lie in the analytic school so you have to write your exams and your assignments in that manner. Don't expect to be deep and philosophical like Hegel and expect to fool him. Precision and conciseness is key.
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Enthusiastic, forgiving and gentle marker on tests. Very knowledgeable.
From his syllabus:  "Do not ever come to me asking what you can do to improve your grade."  This is unsound pedagogy especially at the undergraduate level.

I took his class in the summer. It may seem hard in the beginning but don't worry you will get the hang of it. He explains the material very well, just pay attention and go to class. Don't get intimidated by the amount of work he gives, it's for your benefit & will help u do better on the exam. Overall, he's a nice guy and prof.
